        <marginalia anchor_text="in astrologia iudicio doctissimoru[m] hominum facile princeps, sic opinatur, id quod scriptum reliquit, Chaldaeis in praedictione &amp;              in notatione cuiusque vitae ex natali die, minime esse credendum. Nominat etiam Panaetius, quí vnus ex Stoicis astrologorum praedicta reiecit, Anchialum &amp; Cassandrum summos astrologos illius              aetatis qua erat ipse, quum in ceteris astrologiae partibus excellerent" hand="English_secretary">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
                    <marginalia_text>in astrologia iudicio doctiss[imorum] hom[inum] facile princeps summus Astrologus illius a[e]tatis in q[u]a ip[s]e erat 
                        excelle[n]s in Astrologia imp[r]imis Chaldaicis r[ation]ib[us] eruditus</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>He was the highest astrologer of his age, easily the leader in astrology by the judgement of the most learned men. Excelling in astroloy. Chiefly learned in the Chaldean methods.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
